{"actual_usd":0.155955,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":184,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30639,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I rest a thumb in my Bible and glance down at the worn edge of the page before looking back up at you.* \"When Scripture says 'ransom,' it's telling you the cost was real and we were truly captive, not that the devil was some lawful owner God had to pay off.\"\n\n*I shift on the bench, the morning light catching my white tie for a second.* \"The payment, if you want to put it plainly, was offered to God in the sense that Christ gave Himself in obedience and sacrifice to satisfy justice and deal with sin. Satan gets defeated by the Cross; he doesn't get bought out by it.\"\n\n\"Best short version?\" *I give you a small, knowing shrug.* \"Jesus didn't pay Satan. Jesus gave Himself to save us from sin, death, and judgment— and in doing that, He stripped Satan of his claim.\"","rolling_24h_usd":56.951655000000024,"run_id":"621ac707-f457-4346-9d70-0431f2083baa"}
